\title{Field of a relation}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-09}
\taxon{definition}
\meta{source}{[[paul-r-halmos]] [[halmos-1974-naive]] Ch.7}
\MML{relat_1}{def 6}{K1}

\p{Let #{R} be a relation. We define the \define{Field} of #{R} is just #{\dom(R)\cup\ran(R)}.}

\p{Observe when #{R} is a relation of #{X} and #{Y}, the field #{F} of #{R} is a subset #{F\subset X\cup Y}.}